Following the order of operations (parentheses, exponents, multiplication and division from left to right, and addition and subtraction from left to right), we have
$$\begin{array}{c@{}c@{}c@{}c@{}c@{}}
& & 4 \times 2 &=& 8 \\
+ & 3 & + & 25 & = \\
\cline{1-2}
& & 2 & + & 8 & = \\
& & & + & 25 & = \\
\cline{2-3}
\end{array}$$
So the solution is $\boxed{31}$.
The answer is: 31
